│ The previous edits were intended to guard the copysign propagation against    │
│ nnan to avoid introducing poison, but intermediate changes caused             │
│ instability. I will now provide a clean, minimal patch that fixes the         │
│ original bug without altering other behaviors.                                │
│                                                                               │
│ Patch summary:                                                                │
│ - In InstCombine’s copysign handling, only perform the nested copysign        │
│ sign-argument propagation if it is safe with respect to nnan: specifically,   │
│ if the outer copysign does not have nnan or we can prove the propagated sign  │
│ operand cannot be NaN using ValueTracking.                                    │
│ - Do not attempt to drop fast-math flags (ninf, nnan) during InstCombine, to  │
│ avoid breaking canonicalization and existing tests.                           │
│ - Do not add any additional guards related to infinity. The original bug is   │
│ caused by nnan, and guarding nnan is sufficient.                              │
│                                                                               │
│ Applied change:                                                               │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCalls.cpp                  │
│ - Modification around the copysign nested call propagation:                   │
│                                                                               │
│ Old:                                                                          │
│   // Propagate sign argument through nested calls:                            │
│   // copysign Mag, (copysign ?, X) --> copysign Mag, X                        │
│   Value *X;                                                                   │
│   if (match(Sign, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::copysign>(m_Value(), m_Value(X))))   │
│     return replaceOperand(*II, 1, X);                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ New:                                                                          │
│   // Propagate sign argument through nested calls:                            │
│   // copysign Mag, (copysign ?, X) --> copysign Mag, X                        │
│   // Be careful with nnan on the outer copysign: replacing the sign operand   │
│   // with X may introduce a NaN operand, which would make the instruction     │
│   // poison under nnan semantics. Only do this if the outer doesn't have nnan │
│   // or we can prove X is never NaN.                                          │
│   Value *X;                                                                   │
│   if (match(Sign, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::copysign>(m_Value(), m_Value(X)))) { │
│     FastMathFlags FMF = II->getFastMathFlags();                               │
│     // Guard against introducing a NaN operand to an nnan outer copysign.     │
│     // Perform the transformation if the outer doesn't have nnan or if        │
│     // we can prove the propagated operand X is never NaN.                    │
│     if (!FMF.noNaNs() ||                                                      │
│         isKnownNeverNaN(X, /*Depth=*/0,                                       │
│ getSimplifyQuery().getWithInstruction(II)))                                   │
│       return replaceOperand(*II, 1, X);                                       │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ This preserves correctness for the reproducer (outer nnan with potentially    │
│ NaN sign operand) and keeps other tests intact by not dropping flags or       │
│ adding unrelated guards.                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ Instructions to verify:                                                       │
│ - Run the test suite focusing on InstCombine and the specific reproducer to   │
│ ensure the transformation is correctly guarded.                               │
│                                                                               │
│                                                                               │
